 abstract and make it concrete. In this class we\\u2019ll show you how to go from no prior coding knowledge to crafting your own dynamic websites using HTML, CSS, JavaScript, PHP and MYSQL.\\r\\n\\r\\n<strong>When<\\/strong>\\r\\nFebruary 19th to 21st, 2016.\\r\\n\\r\\n<strong>Where<\\/strong>\\r\\n[ Only Offline ]\\r\\nIIIT Hyderabad, Gachibowli, Hyderabad, Telangana, Pincode - 500032.\\r\\n<h3>Workshop Highlights<\\/h3><ul><li>Learn and interact with experts in the field of Web Development.\\r\\n<li>Practical demonstration for each and every module mentioned in course contents.\\r\\n<li>Improve your job prospects and get an edge over your counterparts.\\r\\n<li>Receive an unparalleled education on the art of computer security with personal one-to-one attention.\\r\\n<li>Covers all the basics for development of a server side website.\\r\\n<li>Hands on Demonstrations of Latest Animation Techniques & Tools.\\r\\n<\\/ul><h3>Workshop Details<\\/h3><ul><li>All study material would be provided\\r\\n<li>All the necessary softwares would be provided\\r\\n<li>Workshop will be of 18 Hours (3 Days, 6 hrs each)\\r\\n<\\/ul>\\r\\n\\r\\nNote: If you have issues with registration or payment, contact us at <a href=\\\"mailto:webdev@felicity.iiit.ac.in\\\" class=\\\"underlined\\\">webdev@felicity.iiit.ac.in<\\/a>\"'),(790,32,575,'description','\"<h1><strong>Contest has Ended<\\/strong><\\/h1>\\r\\n\\r\\nWelcome to Shakespeare\\u2019s Shaky Pears! The online programming event presented to you by LitCafe, as part of Felicity, IIIT-H. \\r\\n\\r\\nWhy a programming event by LitCafe? Well, because this is a contest which requires you to write your code in Shakespeare\\u2019s Programming Language, an esoteric language which has its syntax resembling Shakespearean plays. The character in the play are variables, and the interactions between the characters onstage delineates interactions between these variables.\\r\\n\\r\\nRead more about it here:\\r\\n<a class=\\\"underlined\\\" href=\\\"h