rd Groove\"'),(1626,124,1193,'tagline','\" \"'),(1627,124,1193,'description','\"Felicity, IIIT Hyderabad presents its headlining act on 29th January Junkyard Groove!!\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you don\'t know about it already, it\'s a decade-old rock metal band that\'s maintained continued presence in the top 10 indie bands in the country. With 2 albums and 2 E.Ps to its credit, Junkyard Groove is best known for its unique music styling laced with catchy hooks and a live wire performance, with none to match. Junkyard Groove has had the honor of opening for bands like Iron Maiden, Megadeath, Prodigy, Machine Head, Mr. Big, and more, in the past.\\r\\n\\r\\nWith Ameeth Thomas leading the vocals and playing the acoustic guitar, Josh Mark Raj with the electric guitar supplying backing vocals, Jitesh James Dharmaraj with bass guitar and Ritesh John Dharmaraj at the drums, we can\'t wait to see them perform on the Felicity Stage!\\r\\n<iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/21QgeyUU20A\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\\r\\nArtist Managed by White Heaven Entertainments Pvt Ltd\\r\\n\\r\\n#felicity17 #ForeverYoung #JunkyardGroove #jyg #pronight\"'),(1628,124,1193,'start_time','\"2017-01-29 21:15\"'),(1629,124,1193,'end_time','\"2017-01-19 23:00\"'),(1630,124,1193,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"'),(1631,124,1193,'contact_email','\"contact@felicity.iiit.ac.in\"'),(1632,124,1194,'description','\"Felicity, IIIT Hyderabad presents its headlining act on 29th January Junkyard Groove!!\\r\\n\\r\\nIf you don\'t know about it already, it\'s a decade-old rock metal band that\'s maintained continued presence in the top 10 indie bands in the country. With 2 albums and 2 E.Ps to its credit, Junkyard Groove is best known for its unique music styling laced with catchy hooks and a live wire performance, with none to match. Junkyard Groove has had the honor of opening for bands like Iron Maiden, Megadeath, Prodigy, Machine Head, Mr. Big, and more, in the past.\\r\\n\\r\\nWith Ameeth Thomas leading the vocals and playing the acoustic guitar, Josh Mark Raj with the electric guitar supplying backing vocals, Jitesh James Dharmaraj with bass guitar and Ritesh John Dharmaraj at the drums, we can\'t wait to see them perform on the Felicity Stage!\\r\\n<\\/br><iframe width=\\\"560\\\" height=\\\"315\\\" src=\\\"https:\\/\\/www.youtube.com\\/embed\\/21QgeyUU20A\\\" frameborder=\\\"0\\\" allowfullscreen><\\/iframe>\\r\\nArtist Managed by White Heaven Entertainments Pvt Ltd\\r\\n\\r\\n#felicity17 #ForeverYoung #JunkyardGroove #jyg #pronight\"'),(1633,125,1196,'name','\"Kaizala Hackathon\"'),(1634,125,1196,'tagline','\" \"'),(1635,125,1196,'description','\"<h2>Introduction<\\/h2><br\\/>\\r\\nExponential growth in mobile penetration and increasing availability of data connectivity has led to widespread adoption of personal communication apps globally. As we move towards a mobile only world we can see an emerging need to enable better collaboration and productivity on mobile devices.\\r\\nWith this in mind Microsoft developed Kaizala, a free messaging and productivity app that helps you get your work done. Kaizala is specially designed to facilitate real-time collaboration and efficient work management. You can read more about it and download it here: http:\\/\\/aka.ms\\/installkaizala\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Problem statement<h2><br\\/>\\r\\nParticipating teams are required to build a solution on the Kaizala messaging platform based on one of the themes mentioned below. Teams may either automate a feature of Kaizala by integrating with an external system using REST based APIs or create custom experiences in the conversation context called mini-apps within Kaizala using HTML\\/JS. For details refer to the technical introduction document provided below. \\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Themes<\\/h2><br\\/>\\r\\n<li>\\r\\nConnected campus: Connect different systems of your campus with your mobile devices. Think about integrating your Library, your Accounts department, your Mess or Hostel with Kaizala to get notifications and alerts or build custom mini-apps to make your campus completely cashless.\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>\\r\\nDigital Education: How can you digitize education at your campus? Get your doubts cleared on your mobile device or Replace Xeroxed notes\\/assignments with digital copies are some of the things we can think of, let\\u2019s see what you can come up with?\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>\\r\\nClub & Event Management: Be it club activities or large events like Felicity, chances of last-minute chaos are always high. What can you build to better plan, manage and execute so that this chaos is avoided?\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n<li>\\r\\nCollege Social: College is where a person\\u2019s social life kick starts in full swing, no? Build mini-apps to enable that. Here are a few ideas from our side \\u2013 plan weekend trips or evening movies, keep track of items or money lent, make plans for someone\\u2019s birthday or just sit and gossip.\\r\\n<\\/li>\\r\\n\"'),(1636,125,1196,'rules','[\"This competition is open only to current students of an educational institute participating in Felicity 2017.\",\"Teams of maximum 3 members are allowed\",\"There will be 2 rounds: <li> Ideation \\u2013 Online, from 19 to 24 Jan 2017, and <\\/li><li>Development \\u2013 At IIITH campus, 10am \\u2013 6pm on Friday, 27 Jan 2017<\\/li>\",\"The winning team will receive a cash prize of INR 5000 per team member and the runners-up will receive a cash prize of INR 3000 per team member. Apart from this all teams selected for the Development round will receive Microsoft certificates. \",\"In the Ideation round teams are required to submit their ideas using the proposal template provided below. \",\"All relevant sections of the Ideation proposal must be complete, incomplete proposals will not be considered.\",\"We have also provided a Sample Proposal below to help you understand how to structure your ideas better.\",\"For details regarding extensibility of the Kaizala platform and development related basic information please refer to the technical introduction document provided below.\",\"The Ideation round will close at 10 am on Tuesday, 24 Jan 2017. All proposals must be emailed to kaizala_hackathon@microsoft.com before this deadline.\",\"Shortlisting will be done based on the Ideation proposal and selected teams will be informed over email.\",\"A team may submit more than one proposal in case it has multiple ideas, however only one proposal per team will be shortlisted.\",\"All members of teams selected for the Development round will need to present for a full-day event from 10am \\u2013 6pm on Friday, 27 Jan 2017 at the IIITH campus.\",\"We reserve the right to use pictures and testimonials from this event for marketing purposes.\"]'),(1637,125,1197,'description','\"<h2>Introduction<\\/h2><br\\/>\\r\\nExponential growth in mobile penetration and increasing availability of data connectivity has led to widespread adoption of personal communication apps globally. As we move towards a mobile only world we can see an emerging need to enable better collaboration and productivity on mobile devices.\\r\\nWith this in mind Microsoft developed Kaizala, a free messaging and productivity app that helps you get your work done. Kaizala is specially designed to facilitate real-time collaboration and efficient work management. You can read more about it and download it here: http:\\/\\/aka.ms\\/installkaizala\\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Problem statement<\\/h2><br\\/>\\r\\nParticipating teams are required to build a solution on the Kaizala messaging platform based on one of the themes mentioned below. Teams may either automate a feature of Kaizala by integrating with an external system using REST based APIs or create custom experiences in the conversation context called mini-apps within Kaizala using HTML\\/JS. For details refer to the technical introduction document provided below. \\r\\n\\r\\n<h2>Themes<\\/h2><br\\/