ial concept art experience designing game assets for high quality 3D games and leading a team of artists in visual development. To get a brief idea of his work, do visit: http:\\/\\/www.rahulphilip.com\"'),(2001,137,1492,'start_time','\"2017-01-28 11:00\"'),(2002,137,1492,'end_time','\"2017-01-28 13:00\"'),(2003,137,1492,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"'),(2004,138,1494,'name','\"Education For All\"'),(2005,138,1494,'tagline','\"Talk\"'),(2006,138,1494,'description','\"The talk is by a renowned and acclaimed educational activist, Mrs.Shukla Bose. She has been running Parikrama foundation where she is trying to bring better teaching and learning opportunities for kids in slums of Bangalore. She has previously spoke about her work at *the TED* and can be viewed here- https:\\/\\/www.ted.com\\/talks\\/shukla_bose_teaching_one_child_at_a_time. Do turn up for the talk, where she will be speaking about \\\"education for all\\\".\\r\\n\\r\\nBrief bio- Shukla Bose is the founder and CEO of the Parikrma Humanity Foundation, a nonprofit organization that runs English-medium schools for under-privileged children in Bangalore, India.\\r\\nShe volunteered with Mother Teresa at Missionaries of Charity for 7 years.Her career began as a teacher in a convent school in Kolkata, and she later moved on to work at an army school in Bhutan. \\r\\nShe has won many accolades, a few of which include- \\r\\nIndira Gandhi Sadbhawana Award, 2014\\r\\nIndia\\u2019s Woman Entrepreneur of the Year, 1995\"'),(2007,138,1494,'start_time','\"2017-01-28 15:30\"'),(2008,138,1494,'end_time','\"2017-01-28 17:00\"'),(2009,138,1494,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"'),(2010,139,1496,'name','\"Women in Social Ventures\"'),(2011,139,1496,'tagline','\"Talk\"'),(2012,139,1496,'description','\"The talk is by a lady who is leading a hand loom revolution in the form of her venture- Malkha. Ms.Uzuramma is an activist, social designer, metal smith when free, and above all , a loving woman with passion and vision for a better tomorrow. Socially responsible ventures are a thing for real and that is what her work is teaching us.\\r\\n\\r\\nBrief Bio: Information about the mission statement, work and vision can be found in the following links.\\r\\nhttp:\\/\\/malkha.in\\/\\r\\nhttp:\\/\\/www.thealternative.in\\/lifestyle\\/the-loomslead-india\\/\\r\\nhttp:\\/\\/malkhaindia.blogspot.in\\/?m=1\\r\\n\"'),(2013,139,1496,'start_time','\"2017-01-28 14:00\"'),(2014,139,1496,'end_time','\"2017-01-28 15:30\"'),(2015,139,1496,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"'),(2016,140,1498,'name','\"Introduction to Active Missile Seeker Systems\"'),(2017,140,1498,'tagline','\"Talk\"'),(2018,140,1498,'description','\"This talk will present various aspects of Missile Seekers with the multiple technologies involved in realizing a seeker, including RF, Antennas, Mechanical, Digital Signal Processing, Power Electronics, Electrical and above all, System Engineering. Requirements and test methods for evaluating a seeker will be discussed. Some demonstration of Indigenous Seekers with results will also be presented during the lecture.\\r\\n\\r\\nSpeaker Bio: Yogesh K. Verma obtained his B.Tech. in Electronics and Telecommunication in 1993 from College of Engg. & Tech., Jamia Millia Islamia, New Delhi and M.Tech. in Microwave Electronics  in 1995 from Department of Electronic Sciences, University of Delhi South Campus, New Delhi. Post M.Tech, he joined Bhabha Atomic Research Centre as Scientific Officer \\u2013 \\u2018SC\\u2019 and later moved to SAMEER Mumbai as Project Associate and later as Scientific Officer.\"'),(2019,140,1498,'start_time','\"2017-01-27 14:00\"'),(2020,140,1498,'end_time','\"2017-01-27 15:30\"'),(2021,140,1498,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"'),(2022,141,1500,'name','\"Comics : Not So Comical\"'),(2023,141,1500,'tagline','\"Talk\"'),(2024,141,1500,'description','\"This talk is the flagship talk of the fest as it captures the essence of being young.\\r\\n\\r\\nFew talks on the \\\"History\\\" of anything are this entertaining. All the way from sequential cave paintings to graphic novels and super weirdos, Rajani Thindiath talks about the evolution of comics. Comics as medium just saying something with lines and scratches on a cave wall. As a medium of protest, or maybe as a bubble of happiness in the midst of the world wars which was ironically the golden age of comics, giving rise to phantom, super man, wonder woman, Pulitzer winning Mauss, a parody on Hitler and the Holocaust. But super heroes are human too, this led to the a darker era of comics that explored the psychological weight of vigilantism and imperfect superheroes, like Watchmen and Batman the killing joke.\\r\\n\\r\\nSpeaker Bio :Rajani Thindiath has been working as the Editor of the popular children\\u2019s magazine Tinkle. She has been involved with comic and story telling for more than a decade now. Armed with ingenuity from developing a best selling magazine and a long standing experience, she will be speaking on the role comics play in developing creativity and fostering imagination.\"'),(2025,141,1500,'start_time','\"2017-01-27 15:00\"'),(2026,141,1500,'end_time','\"2017-01-27 16:30\"'),(2027,141,1500,'venue','\"IIIT Hyderabad\"');
